{"questionId":"2966635","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>S</mi><mo>)</mo></math> to be the maximum product of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> positive real numbers with a sum of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>S</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>S</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>For <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>, the maximum product can be expressed as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>S</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mi>S</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Verify that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>S</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mi>S</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math> is true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>S</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>12</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>36</mn></math>&nbsp;which is the maximum product (from (b)(ii))&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Both the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>36</mn></math> <strong>AND</strong> a link to part (b), which may be simply seeing the word “maximum” must be seen to award the <em><strong>A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2966635","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ1.2c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Verify that M2(S)=S22 is true for S=12.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Simple proof"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}